N>Sebor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(5/22/02 9:46:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> I've read through some of these topics and posts, and i agree with pretty much all of them. Magicians are supposed to be one of the better soloing classes. Yet we cannot solo something until it is about 5-10 levels under us throughout the 30's,40's and 50's. Even when we can solo a mob, we have to deal more than half the dmg or else our pet will take 50% of the xp. With all this, magicians should at least be able to charm, or root/snare. All we need are a few more abilities to balance out our class. Such as stronger pets, or the ability to snare, or better nukes. This would really help the magician's class. I'm not saying all of them should be added to the game, I'm just saying that 1 of the above would be enough. I hope you'd all agree with me on this.<br>
<br>
<br>
P.S. I understand that Verant works hard to keep us all happy, and I don't want to criticize them on how the magician class is unbalanced. But I felt I had to do something about all this. (Example: we can't even solo giants till 44. What's up with that? 10 levels higher than they are) But if someone at Verant is reading this, please, please, please consider it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 727<br> <font color=#333333>(5/22/02 11:05:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> Sebor,<br>
<br>
Soloing power really really really depends on what you are fighting more than how strong you are. I don't know if there are any classes other than Necromancers and perhaps Shadowknights that solo giants well at 44. <br>
<br>
Not only that, but soloing strength and tactics differ from class to class. Necro's fearkite in most wide open places. Magicians can solo harder things by chain casting pets. Bards can solo red cons by charming, or by outright kiting with chants or other AoE/DD songs.<br>
<br>
Besides that, not every class has to solo well to be an extremely potent force in the world. Enchanters, for example, are quite powerfull with their spellset, and contribute.. a ton of damage to any situation through their abilities. However, they don't solo well in many situations (rather, not as well as a Necromancer does, per sae). <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
Conjurer of the 58th Season<BR>
Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 4:11:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> I agree that we are not exactly the best soloers around, but I think that while it would be nice if we were able to consistently solo whites or high blues through to at least 50, I'm more a group-oriented mage, and find that we need to be at least percieved to be more useful in a grp.  Chucking the exp penalty out altogether would help that, since I've still (at 40th lvl) gotten msgs saying that my pet is taking exp from the grp, so the grp doesn't want you.<br>
<br>
There are many issues to mage class balance, and soloing ability should be one of the criteria we should be balanced against other soloing classes with, but it shouldn't be the difinitive one.<br>
 <p>Eriol Telcontar - Dragons Revolt<BR>
Magician of the 40th Summoning<BR>
The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urhionsligo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 564<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 10:09:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Magicians are supposed to be one of the better soloing classe<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
