Conjurer of the 58th Season<BR>
Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uimaginos9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Imaginos9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 452<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 1:49:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> Actually he made a statement some time ago about mages not needing upgrades because we were one of the top soloers.  Then of course Luclin came out and thats all changed.<br>
<br>
Veldin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 714<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 2:11:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> Imag<br>
<br>
Well pre-kunark and even after kunark magicians were very good soloers. Now we are middle of the pack, but I have found some very good spots to solo that have helped to get me to lvl 59.  I can not solo everywhere but who can, and really there are so few good solo areas for &quot;solo classes&quot; to do any more that the solo part of the game is really fading.  It is a shame that people solo in places like Velks because it is better experience and easier then alot of the new outdoor zones. Velks is over run with solo places and it really sucks. Most of the monks on my server that have epics have sol b camped non-stop. Most monks cannot solo in ME or Fungus grove so they are forced to solo in old word dungeons.<br>
<br>
Making pets better will help soloing somewhat BUT if they don't remove the experience penalty and leave the heal spells as is then we going to be no better off solo then we are now. I really don't want my pet doing so much damage &quot;solo&quot; that it outdamages me on kills. On the same note I do want pets upgraded.  The experience penalty is a big problem and really needs to be looked at. <br>
<br>
Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 4:19:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> Straight out of the EQ Trilogy Manual:<br>
<br>
&quot;There are some classes that are quite good at soloing, however.  Both the magician and necromancer classes get pet spells which allow them to summon an elemental or skeleton respectively. ... Other classes can solo to some extent, but these four are the champs.&quot;<br>
<br>
I left out the sections about the druid and shaman.  This block clearly shows, even after Velious, VI either wanted, or realized Mages are one of the top soloers.  But unfortunately they haven't kept it that way, or it was only really PERCIEVED anyways, and not as true as they thought.<br>
<br>
So that's where VI said that Mages were one of the top soloers Rhion.<br>
 <p>Eriol Telcontar - Dragons Revolt<BR>
Magician of the 40th Summoning<BR>
The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchakkolio.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chakkolio</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 7:04:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> Why is there so much class envy?  Mages want snare/root so they can solo like Wizards/Druids.  They want better pet heals.  They want more powerful nukes.  They want pet XP penalty removed.  Do the people that make these request think about the overall picture?<br>
<br>
Take away the pet XP penalty and what do you have?  A magician that sicks his pet on something, doesnt even nuke, at most casts 1 heal or just chain summons his pet.  Whats the risk or the cost in that?  A stack of Malachites.... damn, thats so tough on the Magician class.  If people didn't exploit AFK camping, then perhaps Verant would do something about the pet XP penalty.  But as long as Magicians will exploit the AFK camping ability, Verant sees no reason to remove the penalty, and let those ppl get so much reward for the lack of risk involved.<br>
<br>
Give mages snare/root and we become even more powerful, and again you take away the risk and up the reward.  I agree that having a mob kill your pet and having Gate as the only true escape is tough, but how much do you people want handed to you on a silver platter?  Try to think outside the box for a second... if Verant gave these things to the Magician class it would be unbalanced... and then other classes would complain, those other classes would get upgrades or Magicians would get nerfs.  This class is never going to be happy no matter what Verant does if you expect to have everything handed to you.<br>
<br>
Yes, I play a magician.  Yes, i find it frustrating at times.  But the game is no fun nor exciting if everything is so easy.  Bloodgills at lvl 45-51 were a joke... 1% risk for the reward of gaining 1 level in a matter of 8-9 hours played (average playtime per day).  So, after 50, Magicians aren't the soloers that they were pre-50.  There has to be a point where the balance takes place... sadly, Verant doesn't know how to spread that over 60 levels, and instead just drops it at level 50, and causes outrage from the players.  I thought 1-50 was relatively easy.  Now 51-60 is tougher, but I can accept that since it would be a waste of my time to have 60 straigh levels of easy experience and little risk.  Some things need work -- Epic quest timesinks, pet damage at the last 5 levels, pet damage mitigation and ATK levels so that we can use our offensive tools on high end mobs.  Giving us snare or root, or taking away the XP penalty so that lazy individuals can exploit it are not things I want Verant to be focusing on for the Magician class. <p><p align="center"><font face="Times New Roman"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7621>Chakkolio<a/><BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchakkolio.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chakkolio</A> at: 5/23/02 7:05:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uimaginos9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Imaginos9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 455<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 7:58:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some major changes need to be made...</span><hr size=1> Wez, <br>
<br>
I totally agree. I started playing eq a bit before kunark and had a great time even after kunark came out and I found myself a bit weaker then prekunark.<br>
<br>
The pet penalty needs to be gone. The comment Alan made about mages was I belive during the first round of class balance talks and recently the same kind of statement in the second round.<br>
<br>
I still don't see how we are top soloers when we suffer this exp penalty yet no other class does for using thier prime abilities...except the poor beastlords.<br>
<br>
Wizards dont suffer a 50% hit when they snare more then one mob at a time, nor do druids.  You don't see that Monk getting a 50% hit when he uses bind wounds and FD to solo.  I don't see that Ranger getting a -50% exp adjustment when he snares and shoots that bow <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  etc....<br>
<br>
